description: Unique and rustic private retreat tucked amongst redwood and eucalyptus groves. This is truly a home like no other. Meander up a flagstone path through the trees to the main house, which is a collection of cabin, southwest and old west styles featuring open beam, wood cathedral ceilings, tree trunk pillars, stone floors, leather french door handles, adobe style bedroom fireplaces and artistic stain glass windows. The kitchens have copper countertops, antique-style ranges and natural wood cabinetry. Wander the secret garden that surrounds the property, finding a rock bottom pond with waterfall, raised, irrigated planter beds, grotto style pool, flagstone fire pit, outdoor fireplace and plenty of manicured spaces to relax and reflect. The guesthouse mirrors the charm of the main house with cathedral ceilings, fireplace, kitchen and bath. Enjoy living as if you are always on a get away. This home also has perfect vacation rental potential.

description: Stunning Riverlake home offers high ceilings with an open floor plan, lake views and a boat dock. The kitchen, informal dining area and family room are all open to one another with direct access to the backyard and views of the lake. The gorgeous kitchen has a center island, extensive cabinets, neutral granite counter tops, stainless steel appliances and a large picture window. All four bedrooms are upstairs. description: Traditional showings are still welcome! Buyers can view home in person while practicing social distancing. Or join a live video call with an agent and walk through the home. Every REX home comes with a 30-day buyback guarantee. Terms and conditions apply. Light & airy two-story home in a wonderful location on a large & private cul-de-sac lot with 4 bedrooms, 3 baths, and 2,032 square feet in Orangevale! This home features RV access, newer exterior paint & (2018) HVAC system installed by Clarke and Rush, and a large master bedroom with bay window and view of the picturesque backyard. Tiled entryway leads into a spacious formal living & dining room with vaulted ceilings and large windows that flood the space in natural light. Eat-in kitchen overlooks the family room, creating the ideal setup for entertaining and features tile floors, oak cabinets, recessed lighting, and breakfast nook. Large family room offers a wet bar and cozy brick fireplace, perfect for chilly evenings at home! Completing the main floor is a full bathroom and guest bedroom. Remaining bedrooms are located upstairs, including the tranquil master suite, complete with high ceilings, fan fixture, built-in window seat, and en-suite bathroom with dual vanity, walk-in closet, and an oversized tub/shower combo. Mature shade trees surround the sprawling backyard, making it feel very private and serene. A beautiful redwood deck is the ideal spot for outdoor dining! Two-car garage & RV pad accessed through side fence to the backyard. Fantastic neighborhood with park and excellent schools near shopping & restaurants. Don't miss it!

If you have always dreamed of owning a new home, Elverta Park in Antelope presents the opportunity to own a stunning home to call your own while building a lifetime of memories with your family. Come tour the model homes and find out more about Elverta Park and the many benefits this charming community has to offer. Surrounded by large oak trees, the homes are designed to integrate right into the natural terrain, taking advantage of the short commute to Roseville or the Sacramento core area makes Elverta Park the perfect place to come home to after work. Enjoy the convenience of living just minutes away from the Dry Creek Bike Trail, Cherry Island Golf Course, Antelope Greens Golf Course, local parks, and more. Our new home community is located within a proximity of 1.5 miles to Gibson Ranch, which is a beautiful regional park with over 300 acres offering a large variety of activities including, hiking, sports, fishing, biking, farm animals and much more. Elverta Park is conveniently located next to nearby golf courses, shopping, dining and approximately only 15 miles from the Sacramento International Airport. Summary of Rental Qualifications and Application Process: Required Information - 1. Government issued ID; 2. Last 2 months of pay stubs (If paid weekly, submit last 8 pay stubs. If paid bi-weekly or semi-monthly, submit last 4 pay stubs) -OR- if self-employed, submit Schedule 1040 of last 2 years of Federal tax returns. Application Fees - $45 non-refundable application fee must be paid for each occupant 18 years of age or older. If advertisement specifies that pets are accepted, no more than 3 pets will be permitted. If approved, an increased deposit and monthly pet rent of $50 per pet will be required. Felonies or criminal charges related to illegal manufacture or distribution of a controlled substance, bodily harm or destruction of property, or any sexual related offenses will be cause for a denied application. Time is of the Essence - Applications are processed in the order they are received. The first complete and qualified application will be awarded the right to lease the property.
